Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) have gained significant attention as highly efficient energy conversion devices.
Titulo: Boosting Electrochemical Performance of a Nanocomposite Ni-GDC Anode via Oxygen Vacancy and Ni Dispersion Modulation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Enhancing the overall performance of SOFCs relies on the development of efficient anode materials.
Titulo: Boosting Electrochemical Performance of a Nanocomposite Ni-GDC Anode via Oxygen Vacancy and Ni Dispersion Modulation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, an impregnation approach is proposed to improve the electrochemical performance of the nanocomposite Ni-GDC anode by modulating oxygen vacancies and Ni dispersion.
Titulo: Boosting Electrochemical Performance of a Nanocomposite Ni-GDC Anode via Oxygen Vacancy and Ni Dispersion Modulation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This method successfully achieves well-dispersed Ni nanoparticles and adequate oxygen vacancies in the NiO-GDC anode, resulting in excellent TPBs and catalytic activity for SOFCs.
Titulo: Boosting Electrochemical Performance of a Nanocomposite Ni-GDC Anode via Oxygen Vacancy and Ni Dispersion Modulation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The NiO-GDC nanocomposite exhibits a significant improvement in electrochemical activity, reaching a peak power density of 0.37 W/cm(2) at 850 degrees C. Moreover, it demonstrates remarkable durability with a degradation rate of only 0.1%/h at -380 mA/cm(2).
Titulo: Boosting Electrochemical Performance of a Nanocomposite Ni-GDC Anode via Oxygen Vacancy and Ni Dispersion Modulation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This study provides valuable insights into the modulation of oxygen vacancies and Ni dispersion in nanocomposite Ni-GDC anodes, underscoring their potential as high-performance materials for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Boosting Electrochemical Performance of a Nanocomposite Ni-GDC Anode via Oxygen Vacancy and Ni Dispersion Modulation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These findings contribute to the advancement of superior anode materials with improved electrochemical performance, holding tremendous potential for the development of more efficient and reliable SOFCs.
Titulo: Boosting Electrochemical Performance of a Nanocomposite Ni-GDC Anode via Oxygen Vacancy and Ni Dispersion Modulation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
